claim.claim-text:
1. A recording medium for recording information comprising:
a first area for recording contents data of said disk by a predetermined code;
a second area other than the first area, said second area having frames including a frame sync byte and data bytes;
wherein said data bytes include a sync part and a data part, and
wherein said data bytes are modulated from two data bits to generate a sync pattern of three channel bits followed by four data channel bits for the data part.

13. A method for recording data onto a recording medium having a first area for recording contents data and a second area other than the first area, wherein information is recorded into the first area for recording contents data of said disk by a predetermined code, said method comprising:
rotating said recording medium;
recording information onto said recording medium such that said second area has frames including a frame sync byte and data bytes;
wherein said data bytes include a sync part and a data part, and
wherein said recording includes modulating said data bytes from two data bits to generate a sync pattern of three channel bits followed by four data channel bits for the data part.

19. A reproduction apparatus for reproducing data from a recording medium having a first area for storing contents data and a second area other than the first area, wherein information is recorded into the first area for recording contents data of said disk by a predetermined code, said apparatus comprising:
a driver operable to rotate said recording medium;
a reproduction unit operable to reproduce information from said recording medium;
said second area having frames including a frame sync byte and data bytes;
wherein said data bytes include a sync part and a data part, and
wherein said reproduction unit includes a demodulation unit configured to demodulate said data bytes which had been modulated from two data bits to generate a sync pattern of three channel bits followed by four data channel bits for the data part.

25. A method for reproducing data from a recording medium having a first area for storing user data and a second area other than the first area, wherein information is recorded into the first area for recording contents data of said disk by a predetermined code, said method comprising:
rotating said recording medium;
reproducing information from said recording medium;
said second area having frames including a frame sync byte and data bytes;
wherein said data bytes include a sync part and a data part, and
wherein said reproducing includes demodulating said data bytes which had been modulated from two data bits to generate a sync pattern of three channel bits followed by four data channel bits for the data part.
